Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and thinly slice into half moon shapes. Peel and finely slice two-thirds of the @garlic cloves{3}, peel and grate the remaining third (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium-low heat. Once hot, add your onion and sliced garlic. Cook for about ~{10-15%minutes}, stirring occasionally, until soft.

> Add a splash of water if they start to catch. Your onion should be very soft and lightly golden when done.

While your onion and garlic are cooking, roughly chop the @mint{1/2}(roughly chopped) and @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(roughly chopped). Cut the @spring onion{3} in half lengthways and finely chop - use both white and green parts.

When your onion is soft, add the @ground turmeric{3/4%tsp}, @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp} (go easy on the chilli if you don't like spice!), a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} to your onion mixture and cook for ~{1%minute}. Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1}(drained and rinsed) and add to the saucepan, turn the heat up to medium and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the @flour{16%g} and cook for another ~{2%minutes}, stirring frequently.

Add your mint, parsley, spring onion, @baby spinach{1/2%bunch}, @vegetable stock pot{1} and @water{400%ml}. Raise the heat to high and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for ~{15%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

While your soup is simmering, juice half the @lemon{1} and add to a #small serving bowl{}. Mix in the @Greek style yoghurt{1/2%cup}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and some of your grated garlic.

> The amount you add depends on how garlicky you like things!

Preheat your #grill{} to high, cut the @ciabatta{2} in half and grate the @smoked cheese{40%g}. Grill your ciabatta on one side for ~{30-60%seconds}, then remove, turn over, cover with your cheese and grill until your cheese is melted and bubbling. Remove from your grill and slice each ciabatta into quarters.

Taste your soup and add salt and black pepper if necessary, then serve garnished with big dollops of your garlicky lemon yoghurt and your smoked cheese ciabatta for dipping.